LAGOS – Prince Ademola Waliyullah Adunola has expressed his interest to contest the forthcoming APC primaries and ultimately in the 2023 General election as a Member, Lagos House of Assembly, representing Ifako-Ijaiye 02 on the platform of the All Progressives Congress APC. Prince Adunola expressed his wish through a letter transmitted to the good citizens of the constituency, where he respectfully notified them of his intention to contest for the office. He said, “I am in the race due to the ever-increasing changes in the political arena which requires people with my pedigree to make quality representation and informed legislative decisions as it affects our constituents. “There is no better time than now to share and contribute my wealth of experience in the development of Ojokoro LCDA and Lagos State at large through robust and dynamic legislative representation,” he said. Prince Ademola Adunola said this decision was after wide consultation with his family, friends, business and political associates, traditional, religious and youth leaders. Speaking further, he said, “I hereby seek your unalloyed, practical and unflinching support towards repositioning our Constituency for the better. “I count on your usual support and partnerships, for your votes are my strength.”